com/10-years-ago-sony-redefined-the-modern-console-war-1851031762?_gl=1*1mf3bz1*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczOTkwNzA1OC40OTAuMS4xNzM5OTA3MTQ5LjM0LjAuMA..\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/10-years-ago-sony-redefined-the-modern-console-war-1851031762?_gl=1*1mf3bz1*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczOTkwNzA1OC40OTAuMS4xNzM5OTA3MTQ5LjM0LjAuMA..\"\u003edecades-long battle\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e between mulitple companies and their plastic game boxes—ended a few years ago. And while Sony continues to fight on with its PlayStation despite the war being over, Xbox CEO Phil Spencer recently confirmed that, yeah, it’s all over, and the company is no longer trying to steal users away with exclusives.  - Zack Zwiezen \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/xbox-ceo-phil-spencer-console-wars-over-ps5-switch-era-1851765304\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/xbox-ceo-phil-spencer-console-wars-over-ps5-switch-era-1851765304\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898\" data-recommend-id=\"image://889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1600\" data-height=\"900\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Fantastic Four rides through New York City.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Fantastic Four rides through New York City.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"The Fantastic Four rides through New York City.\" data-chomp-id=\"889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"900\" data-alt=\"The Fantastic Four rides through New York City.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Marvel\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898\" data-recommend-id=\"image://889ed87d3ae00e371221634dc9577898\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1600\" data-height=\"900\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Fantastic Four rides through New York City.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eOn February 18, NetEase \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-netease-game-director-layoffs-season-2-1851765290\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-netease-game-director-layoffs-season-2-1851765290\"\u003elaid off \u003cem\u003eMarvel Rivals\u003c/em\u003e development team members\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, including game director Thaddeus Sasser, just two months after its incredibly successful launch. The hero shooter has been such a runaway success that the news blindsided people across the video game industry. According to a statement the company issued to \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://bsky.app/profile/stephentotilo.bsky.social/post/3lij3gxn2l22g\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/stephentotilo.bsky.social/post/3lij3gxn2l22g\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eGame File\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, NetEase made these cuts “for organizational reasons and to optimize development efficiency for the game.” The layoffs specifically affected the support team based in Seattle while the “core” Guangzhou-based team “remains fully committed to delivering an exceptional experience.” - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-netease-layoff-reaction-seattle-developer-1851765418\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-netease-layoff-reaction-seattle-developer-1851765418\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061\" data-recommend-id=\"image://8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"2560\" data-height=\"1440\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Two of Avowed\u0026#39;s companions, probably about to say something inane.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Two of Avowed\u0026#39;s companions, probably about to say something inane.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Two of Avowed\u0026#39;s companions, probably about to say something inane.\" data-chomp-id=\"8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1440\" data-alt=\"Two of Avowed\u0026#39;s companions, probably about to say something inane.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Obsidian Entertainment / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061\" data-recommend-id=\"image://8aea4545bee04ed34140b3822c489061\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"2560\" data-height=\"1440\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Two of Avowed\u0026#39;s companions, probably about to say something inane.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e“Another win, but who’s counting?” It’s the stupidest thing a person could say after a fight. No one. No one was counting. Including you, Kai, unless you think “another” is a numeral. Recognizing a win in no sense implies tallying anything. It doesn’t make sense. Stop saying it, man. Just \u003cem\u003estop saying it\u003c/em\u003e. In fact, unless you’ve got something useful to say, maybe don’t say anything at all? - John Walker \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/avowed-companion-barks-battles-obsidian-x