/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhen I played Hazelight’s last game, \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/it-takes-two-the-best-co-op-game-of-the-year-is-comin-1847973764\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/it-takes-two-the-best-co-op-game-of-the-year-is-comin-1847973764\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eIt Takes Two\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003e, \u003c/em\u003eback in 2021, it was with an ex who’d had different ideas about where our relationship should go than I did. This made playing as a squabbling, estranged couple in a co-op platformer more fitting for that moment in my life than I could have anticipated. So it’s funny that Hazelight’s upcoming co-op game, \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://eneba-games.sjv.io/dO70QK\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://eneba-games.sjv.io/dO70QK\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eSplit Fiction\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, also feels timely, this one due to its obvious disdain for corporate slop and art theft at a time when nearly every creative field, including the one I work in now, is dealing with the fallout of AI. - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-preview-josef-fares-ai-hazelight-co-op-1851765494\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-preview-josef-fares-ai-hazelight-co-op-1851765494\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432\" data-recommend-id=\"image://c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Human Torch flies while covered in flames.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Human Torch flies while covered in flames.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"The Human Torch flies while covered in flames.\" data-chomp-id=\"c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"The Human Torch flies while covered in flames.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Marvel / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432\" data-recommend-id=\"image://c7cf48048caa03cef61a0762e0cec432\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Human Torch flies while covered in flames.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Human Torch is \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-balance-patch-human-torch-thing-update-1851765320\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-balance-patch-human-torch-thing-update-1851765320\"\u003ejoining the \u003cem\u003eMarvel Rivals \u003c/em\u003eroster tomorrow\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, February 21, and before the fire-flinging hero has even joined the scrap, fans are already scared. Part of \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eMarvel Rivals\u003c/em\u003e’\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e appeal is that its heroes are powerful, destructive, and unconcerned with the petty matters of balance and fairness. The Human Torch seems to continue this trend, as some of the early playtests have shown the flying hero to be a devastating menace. - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-human-torch-storm-team-up-abilities-1851765650\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-human-torch-storm-team-up-abilities-1851765650\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433\" data-recommend-id=\"image://872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Solas talks to someone off-screen.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Solas talks to someone off-screen.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Solas talks to someone off-screen.\" data-chomp-id=\"872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Solas talks to someone off-screen.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: BioWare / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433\" data-recommend-id=\"image://872237628fc378aef4a3e9fbd8340433\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Solas talks to someone off-screen.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhen you’ve been on the internet as long as I have, you get the distinct displeasure of watching cycles of toxicity repeat themselves ad nauseam, usually over things that don’t matter in the grand scheme of things. The world is on fire and rather than devoting energy to important matters, a subset of the internet will create and participate in online campaigns to harass developers who made a video game they didn’t like. These campaigns go beyond reasonable criticism and veer into attacks on people’s personhood, and sometimes include gleeful celebrations of people losing their jobs after layoffs. - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-mark-darrah-youtube-harassment-1851765832\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-mark-darrah-youtube-harassment-1851765832\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Three grindy ARPG games, one in a field, two on a bridge.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Three grindy ARPG games, one in a field, two on a bridge.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Three grindy ARPG games, one in a field, two on a bridge.\" data-chomp-id=\"b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Three grindy ARPG games, one in a field, two on a bridge.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Iron Lore / Crate Entertainment / Runic / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b84a3e19fdb125824c131a1bb760040e\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Three grindy ARPG games, one in a field, two on a bridge.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eFollowing the success of \u003cem\u003eDiablo IV: Vessel of Hatred\u003c/em\u003e, along with the recurring seasonal themes and fresh start opportunities, enjoying the grind brought to us by Blizzard Entertainment is easier than ever. But sometimes it’s not enough. Say, for example, you finish a season early. What then? Well, you could roll a new character and grind to max level a second time…or you could swap games for a bit while you wait for the next \u003cem\u003eDiablo 4 \u003c/em\u003eseason start date. That’s likely some time in April, so what to do with the next month? Here are a bunch of other ARPGs to enjoy.  - Brandon Morgan \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/diablo-4-path-of-exile-2-grim-dawn-titan-quest-1851765614\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/diablo-4-path-of-exile-2-grim-dawn-titan-quest-1851765614\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
